<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The cat was finally out of the bag on Thursday night when Locky Gilbert picked Irena Srbinovska as his winner on The Bachelor.</p>

<p>And the happy couple has now revealed they are planning to enjoy a road-trip in New South Wales before making the long drive back to Perth to move in together.</p>

<p>'We just want to be together,' 30-year-old Locky gushingly told The Wash before Irena added their plans for the foreseeable future involved them being 'on the road'. </p>

<p>Hitting the road: The Bachelor's Locky Gilbert and Irena Srbinovska have revealed they are planning to enjoy a road-trip in NSW before making the long drive back to Perth to move in together. Pictured together on Friday </p>

<p>'Obviously, we've got out future plans, but right now we just want some alone time,' Locky told the publication. </p>

<p>The pair will most likely have to apply for an exemption to enter Western Australia due to the State's strict COVID-19 border restrictions.</p>

<p>They will then have to quarantine for two weeks at home before being able to travel freely within the State.</p>

<p>Smitten: 'We just want to be together,' 30-year-old Locky gushingly told The Wash before Irena added their plans for the foreseeable future involved them being 'on the road'</p>

<p>On Friday night, Irena explained that they are planning to live together in the same city.</p>

<p>'The plan is that I'm moving over to Perth,' a smiling Irena revealed on The Project. </p>

<p>During Thursday night's gut-wrenching finale, Locky told both Bella Varelis and Irena that he was in love with them - but then had the tricky task of sending one home.</p>

<p>After an emotional break-up with Bella, Locky composed himself and then professed his love for Irena, telling her he couldn't wait to spend the rest of his life with her.</p>

<p>Heartbreak: During Thursday night's gut-wrenching finale, Locky told both Bella Varelis [pictured] and Irena that he was in love with them - but then had the tricky task of sending one home</p>

<p>In a new interview with Who magazine, the happy couple revealed the codenames they used to communicate with each other while the show was airing.</p>

<p>'Mine was as simple as Roger Roger and it had a smiley face,' Locky admitted, referring to the moniker he used to save Irena's number in his phone.</p>

<p>'And Locky was under Doug in my phone,' Irena revealed.</p>

<p>'Douglas is Locky's middle name so that's where I got it from and no one picked up on that!' she explained.</p>

